article.headline: Utah Valley State 77, Texas State 45
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Chris Bailey scored 15 points and had four assists to lead Utah Valley State to a 77-45 win over visiting Texas State Saturday night in the home opener for UVSC. Pierre Thomas added 14 points and seven rebounds for Utah Valley State to give the Wolverines (1-2) their first win of the year. The two teams were tied 16-16 midway through the first half, but UVSC broke the game open by going on a 30-6 run to close out first half and open the second. Sylvester Allison's 3-pointer at the buzzer put an exclamation point on Utah Valley State's 21-6 run to finish the half and put UVSC ahead 37-22 heading into halftime. Things didn't get any better for Texas State (0-2) in the second half. UVSC scored nine straight points in the first 90 seconds to extend its lead to 46-22. Utah Valley State added another 10-0 spurt toward the end of the game to push its lead over 30 points. Texas State shot 29 percent from the field for the game and had only five field goals in the second half. Charles Dotson led Texas State with nine points and 10 rebounds.
